longBusinessSummary: Kish Bancorp, Inc., a diversified financial services company, provides various banking products and services primarily in central Pennsylvania and the surrounding areas. It offers checking, savings, money market, certificates of deposit, individual retirement, and health savings accounts. The company's loan products comprises home equity, personal, student, equipment and term, commercial real estate, agricultural, and professional loans, as well as lines of credit, letters of credit, and mortgage and credit card services. It offers personal insurance products, including auto, homeowners and renters, farm, dwelling fire, flood, umbrella, motorcycle, boat, and recreational vehicles insurance; commercial insurance products, which comprise property, general liability, auto, business owners, workers' compensation, bonding, professional liability, and trucking and transportation insurance, as well as insurance for religious organizations, and farm and agriculture; trust and estate services, including estate administration, investment and trust management, and asset protection; financial solutions that consist of financial planning, risk management, investment planning, financial position analysis, retirement income, and wealth transfer; cash management services; cards; benefits consulting solutions. In addition, the company offers travel services, such as travel planning and insurance; and digital banking services. The company was founded in 1935 and is headquartered in Belleville, Pennsylvania.
